<p>From this definition, we can infer that the job of the <code>History</code> 
object is to keep track of which URLs have been selected in 
previous runs of the program. It uses a <code>PStore</code> object as
its persistence method, but that is mostly an implementation detail.</p>

<p>With an understanding of how <code>Spyglass.load_history_file</code> works and 
what type of object it returns, we can now move on to investigating
the <code>Spyglass.fetch_links</code> procedure:</p>

